Viacom Inc., owner of the
Nickelodeon and MTV cable networks, is open to unbundling
channels and letting consumers choose the ones they want.  Viacom would offer its channels individually if the
economics were right,  Philippe Dauman , chief executive officer
of New York-based Viacom, said today at the All Things D
conference in Dana Point,  California .  To contact the reporter on this story:
